When Can Growth Rates Accurately be Measured?
We investigate sub-leading orders of the classic SEIR-model using contact matrices from modeling
of the Omicron and Delta variants of COVID-19 in Denmark.The goal of this is to illustrate when
thegrowth rate,and byextension the infectiousness,can be accurately measured inanew outbreak，
